{"word":"Jacob","slug":"jacob","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Jacob</b> <a href=\"#/H3290\">H3290</a> <br/> Son of Isaac, and twin brother of Esau<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=25&verse=26'>Gen 25:26</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=24&verse=4'>Jos 24:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=1&verse=34'>1Ch 1:34</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=7&verse=8'>Act 7:8</a><br/> Ancestor of Jesus<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=1&verse=2'>Mat 1:2</a><br/> Given in answer to prayer<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=25&verse=21'>Gen 25:21</a><br/> Obtains Esau's birthright for a mess of pottage<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=25&verse=34'>Gen 25:34</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=58&chapter=12&verse=16'>Heb 12:16</a><br/> Fraudulently obtains his father's blessing<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=27&verse=29'>Gen 27:29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=58&chapter=11&verse=20'>Heb 11:20</a><br/> Esau seeks to slay, escapes to Padan-Aram<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=27&verse=46'>Gen 27:46</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=28&verse=5'>Gen 28:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=28&chapter=12&verse=12'>Hos 12:12</a><br/> His vision of the ladder<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=28&verse=22'>Gen 28:22</a><br/> God confirms the covenant of Abraham to<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=28&verse=22'>Gen 28:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=15'>Gen 35:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=16&verse=18'>1Ch 16:18</a><br/> Sojourns in Haran with his uncle Laban<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=29'>Gen 29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=28&chapter=12&verse=12'>Hos 12:12</a><br/> Serves fourteen years for Leah and Rachel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=29&verse=30'>Gen 29:30</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=28&chapter=12&verse=12'>Hos 12:12</a><br/> Sharp practice of, with the flocks and herds of Laban<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=30&verse=43'>Gen 30:43</a><br/> Dissatisfied with Laban's treatment and returns to the land of Canaan<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=31'>Gen 31</a><br/> Meets angels of God on the journey, and calls the place Mahanaim<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=32&verse=2'>Gen 32:2</a><br/> Dreads to meet Esau; sends him presents; wrestles with an angel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=32'>Gen 32</a><br/> Name of, changed to Israel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=32&verse=28'>Gen 32:28</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=10'>Gen 35:10</a><br/> Reconciliation of, with Esau<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=33&verse=4'>Gen 33:4</a><br/> Journeys to Succoth<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=33&verse=17'>Gen 33:17</a><br/> Journeys to Shalem, where he purchases a parcel of ground from Hamor, and erects an altar<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=33&verse=20'>Gen 33:20</a><br/> His daughter, Dinah, humbled<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=34'>Gen 34</a><br/> Returns to Beth-El, where he builds an altar, and erects and dedicates a pillar<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=7'>Gen 35:7</a><br/> Deborah, Rebekah's nurse, dies, and is buried at Beth-El<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=8'>Gen 35:8</a><br/> Journeys to Ephrath; Benjamin is born to; Rachel dies, and is &#187;buried in the way to Ephrath, which is Bethlehem&#171;<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=19'>Gen 35:19</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=48&verse=7'>Gen 48:7</a><br/> Erects a monument at Rachel's grave<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=20'>Gen 35:20</a><br/> The incest of his son, Reuben, and his concubine, Bilhah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=22'>Gen 35:22</a><br/> List of the names of his twelve sons<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=26'>Gen 35:26</a><br/> Returns to Arbah, the city of his father<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=27'>Gen 35:27</a><br/> Dwells in the land of Canaan<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=37&verse=1'>Gen 37:1</a><br/> His partiality for his son, Joseph, and the consequent jealousy of his other sons<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=37&verse=4'>Gen 37:4</a><br/> Joseph's prophetic dream concerning<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=37&verse=11'>Gen 37:11</a><br/> His grief over the loss of Joseph<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=37&verse=35'>Gen 37:35</a><br/> Sends into Egypt to bury corn<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=42&verse=2'>Gen 42:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=43&verse=14'>Gen 43:14</a><br/> His grief over the detention of Simeon, and the demand for Benjamin to be taken into Egypt<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=42&verse=36'>Gen 42:36</a><br/> His love for Benjamin<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=43&verse=14'>Gen 43:14</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=44&verse=29'>Gen 44:29</a><br/> Hears that Joseph still lives<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=45&verse=28'>Gen 45:28</a><br/> Removes to Egypt<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=46&verse=7'>Gen 46:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=12&verse=8'>1Sa 12:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=105&verse=23'>Psa 105:23</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=7&verse=15'>Act 7:15</a><br/> List of his children and grandchildren who went down into Egypt<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=46&verse=27'>Gen 46:27</a><br/> Meets Joseph<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=46&verse=34'>Gen 46:34</a><br/> Pharaoh receives him, and is blessed by Jacob<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=47&verse=10'>Gen 47:10</a><br/> The land of Goshen assigned to<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=47&verse=12'>Gen 47:12</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=47&verse=27'>Gen 47:27</a><br/> Dwells in Egypt seventeen years<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=47&verse=28'>Gen 47:28</a><br/> Exacts a promise from Joseph to buy him with his fathers<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=47&verse=31'>Gen 47:31</a><br/> His benediction upon Joseph and his two sons<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=48&verse=22'>Gen 48:22</a><br/> Gives the land of the Amorites to Joseph<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=48&verse=22'>Gen 48:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=4&verse=5'>Joh 4:5</a><br/> His final prophetic benedictions upon his sons:<br/> - Reuben<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=4'>Gen 49:4</a> <br/> - Simeon and Levi<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=7'>Gen 49:7</a> <br/> - Judah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=12'>Gen 49:12</a> <br/> - Zebulun<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=13'>Gen 49:13</a> <br/> - Issachar<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=15'>Gen 49:15</a> <br/> - Daniel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=18'>Gen 49:18</a> <br/> - Gad<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=19'>Gen 49:19</a> <br/> - Asher<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=20'>Gen 49:20</a> <br/> - Naphtali<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=21'>Gen 49:21</a> <br/> - Joseph<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=26'>Gen 49:26</a> <br/> - Benjamin<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=27'>Gen 49:27</a> <br/> Charges his sons to bury him in the field of Machpelah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=30'>Gen 49:30</a><br/> Death of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=33'>Gen 49:33</a><br/> Body of, embalmed<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=50&verse=2'>Gen 50:2</a><br/> Forty days mourning for<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=50&verse=3'>Gen 50:3</a><br/> Burial of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=50&verse=13'>Gen 50:13</a><br/> Descendants of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=29&verse=35'>Gen 29:35</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=30&verse=24'>Gen 30:24</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=18'>Gen 35:18</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=26'>Gen 35:26</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=46&verse=27'>Gen 46:27</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=1&verse=5'>Exo 1:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=2'>1Ch 2</a><br/> Prophecies concerning himself and descendants<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=25&verse=23'>Gen 25:23</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=27&verse=29'>Gen 27:29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=28&verse=15'>Gen 28:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=31&verse=3'>Gen 31:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=13'>Gen 35:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=46&verse=3'>Gen 46:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=1&verse=8'>Deu 1:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=105&verse=11'>Psa 105:11</a><br/> His wealth<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=36&verse=7'>Gen 36:7</a><br/> Well of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=4&verse=30'>Joh 4:30</a>"}]}